user: What apps are running?
Kai : To find out what apps are running, you can follow these steps:
For Android devices:
1. Go to Settings > Battery and Device care > Battery > Background Usage Limits.
2. Selecting the options under there will show you the apps that can run in the background.
3. You can also go to Settings > Apps > All Apps to see a list of all installed apps.
For Apple devices:
1. Go to Settings > General > Background App Refresh.
2. This will show you a list of apps that are allowed to run in the background.
You can also check the number of active apps running in the background by tapping on the "# active apps" option at the bottom left of your screen (for Android devices).
Please note that these steps may vary depending on your device and operating system. If you need more specific instructions, feel free to ask!
